main event: An unidentified flying object was observed over Cochransville, Pennsylvania for approximately 50 minutes on July 25, 1951.
interesting points: The object was described as circular or oval, grey or white in color and appeared to be rotating., The flight path of the object was reported as not erratic., No sound or exhaust was observed during the sighting., The observation lasted for a total of 50 minutes., The report is part of the Project Blue Book documentation.
